      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. experimental (N=11)",
      "description": "Construct axial stiffness predicted by the FEA ensemble was compared against N=11 experimentally measured values spanning two independent laboratories. The mean experimental stiffness was 387.4 N/mm (SD 22.1 N/mm). The FEA ensemble mean prediction was 374.2 N/mm, yielding a signed percentage difference of −3.4%, well within the pre-specified ±10% acceptance bound. The validation metric E/uval was computed as 0.81, below the 1.96 threshold. This result was produced during the primary validation campaign conducted at FDA CDRH in Q3 2023, using Ansys Mechanical 2023 R1 on a 48-core workstation cluster with mesh convergence confirmed at element size 0.35 mm. Boundary conditions replicated ASTM F1717 fixture geometry as documented in laboratory protocol LP-CDRH-2023-047. The detailed computational log, solver residuals, and post-processing scripts are archived in the project repository under tag v3.2.1. The thoroughness of the experimental and computational campaign gives high confidence in this stiffness comparison result, and the reviewers noted no anomalies in force-displacement trace morphology across all 11 specimens.",
